{"lemma":"حَسْبُ","slug":"حَسْبُ","root":"ح.س.ب","root_slug":"ح-س-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-س-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَسْب","root":"حسب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":11},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["noun","prep","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":20},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7943","n7944"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to calculate, to compute"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to charge, to debit"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to credit"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to take (into account), to take (into consideration), to reckon with"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to attach (importance)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to assume, to think, to suppose, to believe","examples":[{"text":"وَلَا تَحْسَبَنَّ اللَّٰهَ غَافِلًا عَمَّا يَعْمَلُ الظَّالِمُونَ","english":"Do not think that God is unaware of what the wrongdoers do."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to regard, to consider, to deem"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be highly regarded"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَسَبَ (ḥasaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"reckoning, calculation, computing"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thinking, opinion, view"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sufficiency"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"only","examples":[{"text":"قَرَأْتُ ثَلَاثَةَ كُتُبٍ فَحَسْبُ/وَحَسْبُ/حَسْبُ.","english":"I've only read three books (and that's all)."},{"text":"الغالبية العظمى من المسلمين لا يؤمنون فحسب بأن الله رحيم؛ بل يؤمنون بأن الله يدعو البشر إلى الرحمة أيضًا.","english":"The vast majority of Muslims not only believe that God is merciful; they believe that God calls humans to be merciful as well."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَسُبَ (ḥasuba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"measure, extent, degree, quantity, amount","examples":[{"text":"بِحَسَبِ","english":"according to"},{"text":"عَلَى حَسَبِ","english":"according to"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"value"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"high regard, esteem"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"noble descent"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"according to, per, by"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of حَاسِب (ḥāsib)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew חָשַׁב (khasháv), Classical Syriac ܚܫܒ, and Egyptian ḥsb.\n\nAdverbial accusative of حَسَب (ḥasab)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7943","headword_ar":"حَسْبٌ","root":"Hsb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sufficiency."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hasobN","text_ar":"هَسْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasobu","text_ar":"حَسْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a [prefixed] noun (S) [syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafoYu","text_ar":"كَفْىُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is implied in the K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTo","text_ar":"قَطْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or] syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAfiY","text_ar":"كَافِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) or [virtually] meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafaY","text_ar":"كَفَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as a pret. in the sense of an emphatic aor.]; (S, K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakofiY","text_ar":"يَكْفِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) Sb says that it is used to denote the being sufficed, or content. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasobuka dirohamN","text_ar":"حَسْبُكَ دِرْهَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biHasobika dirohamN","text_ar":"بِحَسْبِكَ دِرْهَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which latter the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is redundant; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy sufficiency,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing sufficing thee, is a dirhem;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a phrase which may be used in two ways; as predicating of what is sufficient, that it is a dirhem; and as predicating of a dirhem, that it is sufficient; in which latter case,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bHsbk","text_ar":"بحسبك"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an enunciative put before its inchoative, (as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasobuka","text_ar":"حَسْبُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) so that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dirhem is a thing sufficing thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dirhem is sufficient for thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is shown in a marginal note in my copy of the Mughnee, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or, accord. to the S and K,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dirhem suffices thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Bd (iii. 167),"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bHsbk","text_ar":"بحسبك"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHosibuka","text_ar":"مُحْسِبُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAfiyka","text_ar":"كَافِيكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHosabahu","text_ar":"اَحْسَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafaAhu","text_ar":"كَفَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and is shown to have this meaning by its not importing a determinate signification in consequence of its being a prefixed noun with its complement in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA rajulN Hasobuka","text_ar":"هٰذَا رَجُلٌ حَسْبُكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a man sufficing thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, Msb, K.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasobuka *`lika","text_ar":"حَسْبُكَ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"let that be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sufficient for thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasobuka A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"حَسْبُكَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur viii. 65,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will be, sufficient for thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA. See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasiybuka A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"حَسِيبُكَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasobuka biSadiyqinaA","text_ar":"حَسْبُكَ بِصَدِيقِنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A person sufficing thee is our friend"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is added to denote emphatic praise. (Fr, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) In the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA rajulN Hasobuka mino rajulK","text_ar":"هٰذَا رَجُلٌ حَسْبُكَ مِنْ رَجُلٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a man sufficing thee as a man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supplying to thee the place of any other"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by his excellent qualities], (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mararotu birajulK Hasobika mino rajulK","text_ar":"مَرَرْتُ بِرَجُلٍ حَسْبِكَ مِنْ رَجُلٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I passed by a man sufficing thee as a man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hsbk","text_ar":"حسبك"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an expression of praise, referring to the indeterminate noun ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rjl","text_ar":"رجل"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because, in its case, [what is originally (see below)] an inf. n. ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolN","text_ar":"فِعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[under which term lexicologists, but not grammarians, include the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSodar","text_ar":"مَصْدَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) is rendered, in grammatical analysis, by another word, [i. e., by an act. part. n.,] as though one said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHosibN laka","text_ar":"مُحْسِبٌ لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAfK","text_ar":"كَافٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laka","text_ar":"لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S. [Thus"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hsbk","text_ar":"حسبك"},{"kind":"text","text":"in these two instances is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sifap","text_ar":"صِفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. an epithetic phrase; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn rjl","text_ar":"من رجل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamoyiyz","text_ar":"تَمْيِيز"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. a specificative phrase.]) When the noun to which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hsbk","text_ar":"حسبك"},{"kind":"text","text":"refers is determinate, you put"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hsb","text_ar":"حسب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the accus. case, as a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HAl","text_ar":"حال"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. a denotative of state; as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA Eabodu","text_ar":"هٰذَا عَبْدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hi Hasobaka mino rajulK","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهِ حَسْبَكَ مِنْ رَجُلٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is 'Abd-Allah; being one sufficing thee as a man."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S. [Here"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn rjl","text_ar":"من رجل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is, as before, a specificative phrase.]) [See also 4, the corresponding verb.])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hsb","text_ar":"حسب"},{"kind":"text","text":", in this manner, is used alike as sing. and dual and pl.; (S, K;) being [originally] an inf. n. (S.) It is also used alone, [as a prefixed noun of which the complement is understood,] as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodN Hasobu","text_ar":"زَيْدٌ حَسْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without tenween, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasobiY","text_ar":"حَسْبِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasobuka","text_ar":"حَسْبُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c., meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd is sufficient for me"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; like as one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='aniY zayodN layosa gayoru","text_ar":"جَا=ءَنِى زَيْدٌ لَيْسَ غَيْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa gayoruhu EinodiY","text_ar":"لَيْسَ غَيْرُهُ عِنْدِى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S. [That is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasobu","text_ar":"حَسْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", when thus used, is subject to the same rules as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayoru","text_ar":"غَيْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabolu","text_ar":"قَبْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEodu","text_ar":"بَعْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. when so used.]) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasabN","text_ar":"حَسَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places.       -A2-  Also, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HisobapN","text_ar":"حِسْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Burial"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the dead: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burial"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the dead"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in stones"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a grave cased with stones"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burial"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the dead"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrapped in grave-clothes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHosiybN","text_ar":"تَحْسِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K. [See 2.])"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n7944","headword_ar":"حَسَبٌ","root":"Hsb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHosuwbN","text_ar":"مَحْسُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalN","text_ar":"فَعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafaDN","text_ar":"نَفَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manofuwDN","text_ar":"مَنْفُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Numbered, counted, reckoned, calculated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"computed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A number counted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Amount, quantity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"value."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) Sometimes, (S, L, K,) by poetic license, (S,) and in prose, (L,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasobN","text_ar":"حَسْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, L, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ajoru biHasabi maA Eamilota","text_ar":"الاَجْرُ بِحَسَبِ مَا عَمِلْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biHasobi","text_ar":"بِحَسْبِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The recompense is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be, according to the amount,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"value, of thy work."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yujozaY Almaro'u EalaY Hasabi Eamalihi","text_ar":"يُجْزَى المَرْءُ عَلَى حَسَبِ عَمَلِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be, paid according to the amount,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantity, of his work."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Hasabi maA A^asodayota A_ilaY~a $ukoriY laka","text_ar":"عَلَى حَسَبِ مَا اَسْدَيْتَ اـِلَىَّ شُكْرِى لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasobamaA","text_ar":"حَسْبَمَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Hasabi maA","text_ar":"عَلَى حَسَبِ مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":")]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"According to the amount,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"value, of the benefit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"benefits, that thou hast conferred upon me are my thanks to thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liyakuno Eamaluka biHasabi *`lika","text_ar":"لِيَكُنْ عَمَلُكَ بِحَسَبِ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Let thy deed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"work, be correspondent to the quantity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"number, of that:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adequate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"equivalent, to that."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA biHasabi *aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا بِحَسَبِ ذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is equal in number"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is equivalent, to that."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^adoriY maA Hasabu Hadiyvika","text_ar":"مَا اَدْرِى مَا حَسَبُ حَدِيثِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA qadoruhu","text_ar":"ما قَدْرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I know not what is the value of thy story"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Ks, S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHosanotu A_ilayohi Hasaba AlT~aAqapi","text_ar":"اَحْسَنْتُ اـِلَيْهِ حَسَبَ الطَّاقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Hasabi","text_ar":"عَلَى حَسَبِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~aAqapi","text_ar":"الطَّاقَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I benefited him according to the measure of ability."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b4-  Also ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Grounds of pretension to respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour, consisting in any qualities (either of oneself or of one's ancestors) which are enumerated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recounted, as causes of glorying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility; rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality; honourableness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"estimableness, from whatever source derived:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] originally, (MF,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what one enumerates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recounts, of the deeds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"qualities, in which his ancestors have gloried:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, * K, MF:) secondly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what one enumerates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recounts, of his own deeds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"qualities, in which he glories:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thirdly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what one enumerates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recounts, of any deeds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"qualities, that are causes of his glorying, of whatever kind they be:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"memorable deeds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"qualities, of one's ancestors;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one's own deeds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"qualities, in which he glories;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because they were enumerated, or recounted, by the Arabs in contending, or disputing, for glory; (T, Msb, * TA;) the latter consisting in"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such qualities as courage, and good disposition, and liberality:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what are enumerated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recounted, of generous actions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"qualities:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good actions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct, of oneself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of one's ancestors:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generosity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility, of actions"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"righteous, virtuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good, actions"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good disposition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"religion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piety;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because true nobility consists in religion or piety: (MF:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) because it serves in lieu of true nobility: (TA:) in this sense, and in the sense next preceding, it has no corresponding verb: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAlN","text_ar":"بَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAlN","text_ar":"حَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intellect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"understanding:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF:) and a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relations, consisting of his children and others:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHosaAbN","text_ar":"اَحْسَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Az, Mgh.) Accord. to ISk, (S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasabN","text_ar":"حَسَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karamN","text_ar":"كَرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may pertain to him who has not noble ancestors; but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arafN","text_ar":"شَرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majodN","text_ar":"مَجْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, * K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasabN","text_ar":"حَسَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used elliptically, (Mgh, TA,) [in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasiybN","text_ar":"حَسِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,] for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw HasabK","text_ar":"ذُو حَسَبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*awuw HasabK","text_ar":"ذَوُو حَسَبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otaraY biAlHasabi","text_ar":"اِشْتَرَى بِالحَسَبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bought"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in an honourable manner with respect to himself and the seller:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hsb","text_ar":"حسب"},{"kind":"text","text":", here, is said to be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Has~abahu","text_ar":"حَسَّبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ he honoured him; ” or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusobaAnapN","text_ar":"حُسْبَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ a small pillow ” [because him for whom you put a pillow you honour: see 2]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K","MF","Msb","Sh","Mgh","IAar","TA"]}]}}